# Mise Feature Environment Variables

# Build Arguments
# ===============

# Enable Mise polyglot runtime version manager
INCLUDE_MISE=false

# Mise version (auto-bumped weekly by bin/check-versions.sh)
MISE_VERSION=2026.4.20

# Runtime Environment Variables
# =============================

# Where mise installs runtimes (persisted via the /cache volume)
MISE_DATA_DIR=/cache/mise

# Mise download/build cache
MISE_CACHE_DIR=/cache/mise-cache

# Paths where .mise.toml files are auto-trusted (no `mise trust` prompt).
# Defaults to /workspace, the standard mount point for project source.
MISE_TRUSTED_CONFIG_PATHS=/workspace

# Notes
# =====
#
# Mise complements — it does not replace — the baked-in language features
# (INCLUDE_PYTHON, INCLUDE_NODE, INCLUDE_RUST, etc.). Use the baked-in feature
# when you want a reproducible team baseline burned into the image; use mise
# when a project needs to float its runtime version via `.mise.toml` /
# `.tool-versions`, or when you want on-demand installs of less-common runtimes
# (bun, deno, zig, …) without adding a first-class container feature for each.
#
# Installing runtimes that compile from source (e.g. Python via mise) also
# requires INCLUDE_DEV_TOOLS=true for the build toolchain.
